I"—<p>Did you know, <a href="https://metabox.io/plugins/meta-box-builder/">Meta Box Builder</a> has custom attribute feature can bring you a flexible way to create WordPress custom meta box fields and you can create columns also?</p>

<p>To apply <strong>columns</strong> style for your custom fields, on your field in Edit Meta Box page, click â€œShow Advancedâ€ to show Custom Attribute section then click â€œAdd Attributeâ€.</p>

<p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/0Pyl9U9.png" alt="custom attributes" /></p>

<p>On the <code class="highlighter-rouge">key</code> textbox, enter <code class="highlighter-rouge">columns</code> which will add to <code class="highlighter-rouge">columns</code> attribute to that field, and on the <code class="highlighter-rouge">value</code> textarea, enter the column size. Thatâ€™s based on 12 grids system. For example, if you enter <code class="highlighter-rouge">4</code> to value, then the column will has one third size of row.</p>

<p>After that step, donâ€™t forget to Save Meta Box, see your results.</p>

<p>Note: <a href="https://metabox.io/plugins/meta-box-columns/">Meta Box Columns</a> extension is required to create columns.</p>
